  abstract={The global increase in elderly populations, particularly in China, creates significant healthcare challenges related to age-related diseases. The Aging Biomarker Consortium has initiated the X-Age Project to develop a comprehensive aging evaluation system tailored to the Chinese population. The initiative aims to identify dependable biomarkers and construct composite aging clocks that measure biological age across diverse Chinese cohorts. The project outlines its core objectives, methodological approach, and planned deliverables, encompassing cohort recruitment, standardized sample collection, multimodal data acquisition, and clock model development.},
